title.narrative: National STD/AIDS Control Program

description.narrative: Sri Lanka - HIV - Ministry of Health of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka - MOH. This program has the following goals: Ending AIDS by 2025. The objectives of this program are: To prevent new infections of HIV/STI among key populations, vulnerable populations and the general population. To provide universal access to HIV/STI diagnosis and treatment, care and support services for those infected and affected by HIV/STI. To strengthen strategic information systems and knowledge management for an evidence-based response. To strengthen health systems at different levels and to ensure an effective multi-sector HIV/AIDS/STI response. To provide a supportive environment for easy access and delivery of HIV prevention, diagnosis, treatment and care services for all
